# Pinch-to-Zoom Gesture Algorithm Using Pointer Events

## Overview
The algorithm detects when two pointers move closer together (pinch in/zoom out) or farther apart (pinch out/zoom in) using pointer events.

## 1. Detect Two-Finger Touches

**Cache pointer events** to track simultaneous pointer contacts:

```javascript
// Global vars to cache event state
const evCache = [];
let prevDiff = -1;

function pointerdownHandler(ev) {
  // Cache each pointer contact
  evCache.push(ev);
  log("pointerDown", ev);
}
```

**Check if two pointers are active** in the move handler:

```javascript
if (evCache.length === 2) {
  // Two pointers detected - proceed with gesture detection
}
```

## 2. Calculate Distance Between Pointers

Use the horizontal distance (X-axis) between two pointer positions:

```javascript
// Calculate the distance between the two pointers
const curDiff = Math.abs(evCache[0].clientX - evCache[1].clientX);
```

Properties available on cached events:
- `clientX`, `clientY` - pointer coordinates
- `pointerId` - unique identifier for each pointer
- `pointerType` - "touch", "mouse", "pen"

## 3. Determine Zoom In vs Zoom Out

Compare current distance to previous distance:

```javascript
if (prevDiff > 0) {
  if (curDiff > prevDiff) {
    // Distance increased = Pinch OUT (Zoom IN)
    log("Pinch moving OUT -> Zoom in", ev);
    ev.target.style.background = "pink";
  }

  if (curDiff < prevDiff) {
    // Distance decreased = Pinch IN (Zoom OUT)
    log("Pinch moving IN -> Zoom out", ev);
    ev.target.style.background = "lightblue";
  }
}

// Cache distance for next comparison
prevDiff = curDiff;
```

## 4. Complete Implementation

### Register Event Handlers
```javascript
const el = document.getElementById("target");
el.onpointerdown = pointerdownHandler;
el.onpointermove = pointermoveHandler;
el.onpointerup = pointerupHandler;
el.onpointercancel = pointerupHandler;
el.onpointerout = pointerupHandler;
el.onpointerleave = pointerupHandler;
```

### Pointer Move Handler
```javascript
function pointermoveHandler(ev) {
  log("pointerMove", ev);
  ev.target.style.border = "dashed";

  // Update cached event for this pointer
  const index = evCache.findIndex(
    (cachedEv) => cachedEv.pointerId === ev.pointerId,
  );
  evCache[index] = ev;

  // Check for pinch gesture with two pointers
  if (evCache.length === 2) {
    const curDiff = Math.abs(evCache[0].clientX - evCache[1].clientX);

    if (prevDiff > 0) {
      if (curDiff > prevDiff) {
        log("Pinch moving OUT -> Zoom in", ev);
        ev.target.style.background = "pink";
      }
      if (curDiff < prevDiff) {
        log("Pinch moving IN -> Zoom out", ev);
        ev.target.style.background = "lightblue";
      }
    }

    prevDiff = curDiff;
  }
}
```

### Pointer Up Handler
```javascript
function pointerupHandler(ev) {
  log(ev.type, ev);
  removeEvent(ev);
  ev.target.style.background = "white";
  ev.target.style.border = "1px solid black";

  // Reset distance tracker when fewer than 2 pointers
  if (evCache.length < 2) {
    prevDiff = -1;
  }
}

function removeEvent(ev) {
  const index = evCache.findIndex(
    (cachedEv) => cachedEv.pointerId === ev.pointerId,
  );
  evCache.splice(index, 1);
}
```

### Prevent Default Touch Behavior
```css
body {
  touch-action: none; /* Prevent default touch behavior */
}
```

## Key Points

- **Event Cache**: Maintain an array of active pointer events to track multiple simultaneous touches
- **Distance Calculation**: Use `clientX` coordinates to determine pointer separation
- **Comparison**: Compare current distance to previous distance to detect direction
- **Pointer ID**: Use `pointerId` to track individual pointers across events
- **Cleanup**: Remove events from cache on `pointerup`, `pointercancel`, `pointerout`, or `pointerleave`

[Live Example](https://mdn.github.io/dom-examples/pointerevents/Pinch_zoom_gestures.html) | [Source Code](https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/blob/main/pointerevents/Pinch_zoom_gestures.html)

